(1078, 1078, 1, NULL, '__temp_pcjrnvbxjmqtoolywujtybvtyvdkvgnezeqp', NULL, '{\"032378b9-225f-4ca4-b509-5bf5b952dde2\":\"NARM & Resonant Touch\",\"66af9589-1520-49a8-982e-6ddca319d308\":\"<p><strong>NARM individual sessions</strong> focus on working through patterns of developmental trauma, survival strategies, and identity adaptations, supporting a deeper connection to the authentic self and fostering greater relational and emotional freedom.</p><p><strong>Individual Resonant Touch sessions</strong> bring attention to both developmental dynamics and the deeper currents of life force that sustain and shape the body-mind. Through sensitive presence, therapeutic touch, and relational attunement, we gently engage emotional processes, obstacles to authentic expression, and the release of crystallized patterns held within the system. Sessions typically include physical contact, with the client lying fully clothed on a table, allowing the therapist to offer grounded, attuned touch that supports regulation and coherence. This work unfolds within a space of deep listening and embodied awareness, where the natural intelligence of the system is met with respect and curiosity. Both formats offer a safe, compassionate environment for the organic movement of life energy and the emergence of inner spaciousness and connection.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2>Supervision &amp; Trainings</h2><p><strong>Individual supervisions</strong> support practitioners in their professional development from a relational perspective. NARM individual supervisions focus on the application of NARM principles in therapeutic work, exploring survival patterns, relational dynamics, emotional processing, and the therapists own embodied presence within the clinical setting. Resonant Touch individual supervisions are available for those who have trained in Resonant Touch with me, offering a space to deepen sensitivity to the life force, relational attunement, and awareness of how developmental and survival patterns are held within the body-mind.</p><p><strong>Group supervisions</strong> are self-organized and provide a reflective space to explore therapeutic work in a supportive environment. We address the application of NARM principles in clinical practice, the navigation of countertransference dynamics, working through moments of stuckness, and developing comfort with the unknown. Participants bring case material, clinical questions, and personal reflections, fostering an environment for learning and mutual growth. Group supervisions can also be organized around specific themes related to NARM, offering more specific deep-dive explorations.</p><p><strong>Active coaching</strong> groups offer a guided, experiential environment where participants actively practice applying NARM principles. These groups provide a space for participants to explore their own authentic therapeutic impulses, integrate principles into their personal styles of working, and deepen their embodied understanding of relational healing. The focus is on supporting authentic learning rather than rigid application, with an emphasis on safety, creativity, and natural unfolding.</p><h3>&nbsp;</h3><h2><strong>NARM deepening days</strong></h2><p><i>Exploring the Heart of NARM Through Immersive Practice</i></p><p>NARM Deepening Days are a dedicated space for those who wish to engage more fully with the principles of the NeuroAffective Relational Model (NARM). These days are designed for practitioners, students, and individuals already familiar with NARM who are looking to deepen their embodied understanding of this powerful model for healing developmental and relational trauma.</p><p>Each Deepening Day will focus on a specific theme central to the NARM approach.&nbsp;</p><p>These gatherings are <i>experiential and practice-oriented</i>, combining short teaching segments with reflective exercises, active coaching, and live demo sessions. The intention is to create a safe and focused environment for deepening insight, refining relational skills, and exploring how NARMs principles come alive in the moment-to-moment therapeutic process.</p><ul><li>Life Force beyond Adaptations (online)</li><li>Holding Without Fixing: The Role of Touch in a NARM-Oriented Process (at the venue)</li><li>The Gift of Countertransference Dynamics (online)</li></ul><p><strong>Resonant Touch</strong> <strong>seminars&nbsp;</strong>introduce participants to the core principles and applications of Resonant Touch. Combining experiential exploration and theoretical orientation, these seminars cultivate deeper relational presence, inner spaciousness, and sensitivity to the subtle movements of healing. They are open to all therapists and practitioners who are seeking a more embodied and relational foundation for their work.</p><ul><li>Resonant Touch Deepening Day  June 11th, Berlin</li><li>Resonant Touch Intruduction Seminar&nbsp;  October 1315, Berlin</li></ul><p><strong>Resonant Touch therapy days</strong> offer opportunities for individuals to experience personal Resonant Touch sessions outside of my primary practice in Slovenia. By invitation, I travel to different parts of Europe to offer sessions, making this work accessible to a broader community and creating opportunities for direct engagement with Resonant Touch in a more intimate, focused setting.</p><ul><li>Resonant Touch Therapy Days  July 2526, Hannove</li></ul>\"}', 1, '2025-07-23 11:19:30', '2025-07-23 11:19:30', 'cdafd6e2-82de-4c10-9577-8f23c22328d8'),
