(1265, 1265, 1, NULL, '__temp_wjenxdytewgpkoxotzfmwvcsmgqiilfwmfjz', NULL, '{\"032378b9-225f-4ca4-b509-5bf5b952dde2\":\"Resonant Touch Learning Spaces, SV, Group-SV, Active Coaching, NARM Deepening Days\",\"66af9589-1520-49a8-982e-6ddca319d308\":\"<p><strong>Resonant Touch Learning Spaces</strong></p><p>Emerging from years of embodied therapeutic work, including NARM and Biodynamic Craniosacral Therapy, these learning spaces invite presence, curiosity, and experiential exploration. Rather than offering a fixed method, Resonant Touch opens a field of relational depth where healing unfolds through subtle awareness, resonance, and trust in the natural intelligence of the moment.</p><p>The learning currently unfolds in two formats:&nbsp;<strong>Resonant Touch Immersions</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>Resonant Touch Circles</strong>. These spaces support embodied integration, shared inquiry, and intuitive attunement.</p><p>New Resonant Touch Circles may be offered in the future, creating further opportunities for ongoing exploration. For now, these two formats hold the current expression of Resonant Touch learning.</p><p><strong>Resonant Touch Immersions</strong>&nbsp;are three-day experiential gatherings that introduce participants to the foundational principles of Resonant Touch. These immersions are relational and body-basednot focused on technique, but on sensing, presence, and intuitive engagement. Grounded in a biodynamic orientation to life force and the developmental insights of NARM, the work unfolds through attunement, shared reflection, and embodied inquiry.</p><p><strong>Resonant Touch Circles</strong>&nbsp;are longer-term group spaces, held over time, where a deeper exploration of the work takes place. The first of these began in 2022 and continues as a living field of ongoing inquiry and co-creation. These spaces are not trainings, but relational containers in which the approach itself continues to evolve and take shape through shared experience and trust in the unknown.</p>\",\"489bc2dc-2ddb-441d-8ddb-00351993c722\":false}', 1, '2025-08-11 10:25:58', '2025-08-11 10:25:58', '8f4cdc82-84ee-40af-b125-027bb7c75a6b'),
(1266, 1266, 1, 'About Me', 'about-me', 'about-me', '{\"3da30d7e-ecb1-4689-b813-cf5e010cefbc\":{\"titleRaw\":{\"1\":\"About me\"},\"descriptionRaw\":\"\",\"keywords\":[],\"score\":\"\",\"social\":{\"twitter\":{\"handle\":null,\"title\":\"About Me - Karima Hoevar\",\"imageId\":\"\",\"description\":[]},\"facebook\":{\"handle\":null,\"title\":\"About Me - Karima Hoevar\",\"imageId\":\"\",\"description\":[]}},\"advanced\":{\"robots\":[],\"canonical\":\"\"}}}', 1, '2025-08-11 10:26:56', '2025-08-11 10:26:56', '4cd50d25-ae80-41c7-b492-c398bdee143f'),
(1267, 1267, 1, NULL, '__temp_lekvchmjekxlrsvnukjweeivpobcycywklae', NULL, '{\"61d1d186-dff7-4cbd-b901-256e496e4472\":\"About Karima\",\"5b3cf7ba-6a30-467b-8e4d-220f4e2b9105\":\"left\",\"329bb1a1-e734-46d1-8cb5-c3d843e6e98a\":true,\"e5c63454-6cc2-464a-857b-f5eb1ee3d2b2\":\"Karima Valentina Hoevar\",\"5f2d23e1-9a53-4f0f-8982-2bbfc0814ee8\":\"<p>From an early age, I have been deeply attuned to human relationshipsthe ways we connect, misunderstand, and heal. My sensitivity to the spaces between people, shaped by early experiences, led me on a journey of self-inquiry, acceptance, and mindfulness. This path evolved into a professional commitment to trauma-informed therapeutic approaches. I have spent years studying and integrating various therapeutic modalities, always with an emphasis on cultivating presence, inner spaciousness, and relational attunement.</p><p>Since 2011, I have been teaching and co-teaching seminars on Biodynamic Craniosacral Therapy (BCST) in Slovenia and internationally. My work with BCST has provided insights into the bodys inherent wisdom and capacity for self-regulation. Since 2015, I have been part of the teaching team and a supervisor for NeuroAffective Relational Model (NARM) trainings across Europe. I am currently participating in Time Wisdom Training (TWT), facilitated by Thomas Hbl.</p><p>Throughout the years of practice, I am in the process of developing a process-oriented therapeutic approach called <strong>Resonant Touch</strong>, which integrates my understanding of wholeness with principles from NARM and BCST.</p><p>I currently live and work in Ljubljana, Slovenia, where I hold my private practice. While Ljubljana is my main base, I regularly travel due to my teaching and therapeutic work. I occasionally offer sessions in Germanyprimarily in Berlinwhen invited, creating opportunities for in-person connection beyond my home practice.</p>\"}', 1, '2025-08-11 10:26:56', '2025-08-11 10:26:56', 'd1dc3018-53ac-4a65-8817-e86d460797f5'),
(1270, 1270, 1, 'Resonant Touch', 'resonant-touch', 'resonant-touch', '{\"3da30d7e-ecb1-4689-b813-cf5e010cefbc\":{\"titleRaw\":{\"1\":\"My work\"},\"descriptionRaw\":\"\",\"keywords\":[],\"score\":\"\",\"social\":{\"twitter\":{\"handle\":null,\"title\":\"Resonant Touch - Karima Hoevar\",\"imageId\":\"\",\"description\":[]},\"facebook\":{\"handle\":null,\"title\":\"Resonant Touch - Karima Hoevar\",\"imageId\":\"\",\"description\":[]}},\"advanced\":{\"robots\":[],\"canonical\":\"\"}}}', 1, '2025-08-11 10:27:38', '2025-08-11 10:27:38', '8d93a554-b908-495d-b55f-f09f72fe4cf0'),
(1271, 1271, 1, NULL, '__temp_rdwpgnoshteyuhouyaspadhgmvixaknbgkro', NULL, '{\"61d1d186-dff7-4cbd-b901-256e496e4472\":\"Resonant Touch - Holistic Relational Trauma Integration\",\"5b3cf7ba-6a30-467b-8e4d-220f4e2b9105\":\"right\",\"329bb1a1-e734-46d1-8cb5-c3d843e6e98a\":true,\"5f2d23e1-9a53-4f0f-8982-2bbfc0814ee8\":\"<p><strong>Resonant Touch</strong> is an intuitive relational approach to therapy that helps clients realign with their natural inner spaciousness and sense of connection. It is a culmination of my lifelong inquiry into the interplay between mind, body, and relational presence. It is rooted in an embodied awareness of the profound intelligence that guides healing from within.</p><p>The approach centers on creating safe, attuned spaces where healing unfolds organically. Drawing from NARM and BCST, <strong>Resonant Touch</strong> developed as a way to integrate verbal and non-verbal therapeutic approaches. It is grounded in the embodied recognition that we are inherently whole, even in the face of the separation that comes from early adaptations and survival strategies.</p><p><strong>Resonant Touch</strong> recognizes that the path toward healing requires attunement to the complexities of early life adaptations, addressing both the visible and invisible aspects of human experience. The fundamental assumption we offer is that, on a deeper level of experience, we are always whole and complete. Even within the limitation of our adaptations, there is an underlying health at work. Every survival strategy, no matter how misaligned it may appear, is part of an inherent organizing wisdom.</p>\"}', 1, '2025-08-11 10:27:38', '2025-08-11 10:27:38', '657df6e5-b098-405b-aa5e-1c1bf4594c36'),
