(1362, 1362, 1, NULL, '__temp_gjhkorpfqxodozduebcfnlnitpldxvyslcqa', NULL, '{\"49e3e828-6795-49c5-a82b-3360a0b3664d\":\"A three-day journey into the living field of Resonant Touch\",\"eca88837-37fe-4366-9c04-3b186a4046b3\":\"<p>This immersion offers a relational and embodied space for therapists and practitioners to explore the essence of Resonant Touch. Its not a method to learn, but a shared inquirywhere body, presence, and awareness meet in the moment.</p><p>The work draws from two complementary sources:<br><strong>Biodynamic&nbsp;Craniosacral&nbsp;Therapy</strong>, with its orientation to the subtle forces of life and healing, and the&nbsp;<strong>NARM approach</strong>&nbsp;to developmental trauma, which brings awareness to our patterns of self-relation and connection.</p><p>Together, we attune to the quiet intelligence at the heart of all healing. In this space, curiosity, connection, and spaciousness can naturally unfold.</p><p style=\\\"margin-left:0cm;\\\"><strong>What We Will Explore</strong></p><p>We begin by sensing the deeper intelligence of life forcea subtle, organizing movement within and around us. In the craniosacral tradition, this force supports coherence, wholeness, and healing.</p><p>As we meet it with presence and grounded awareness, we listen and respond rather than do or fix. The bodys own healing impulses can then emerge and be met.</p><p>Informed by NARM, we also explore how early adaptations shape our sense of selfand how these patterns live in our present-day therapeutic presence. We approach self-relation not as a concept, but as a lived experienceone that can shift when met with resonance, compassion, and inner safety.</p><p>Throughout the immersion theoratical input and perspectives are provided as orienting principles, and it largely experience-based.&nbsp;You are invited to trust your intuitive impulses and explore how they can be included with sensitivity and care.</p><p>An essential part of the work is about&nbsp;returning to your own sensing, being, and relating.</p>\",\"dffe5daa-5f43-4e4c-bde7-1f63fafb21af\":\"<p style=\\\"margin-left:0cm;\\\"><strong>For Whom?</strong></p><p>This immersion is for:</p><ul><li>Therapists and healing practitioners (psychotherapists, bodyworkers, coaches)</li><li>Professionals working relationally with others</li><li>Anyone drawn to embodied, trauma-informed healing grounded in presence and subtle awareness</li></ul>\",\"50fd66aa-669e-462b-bfb3-183483ca7f53\":{\"date\":\"2025-10-10 07:00:00\"},\"3699bcd1-9095-4053-972b-820dc7fdd9fb\":{\"date\":\"2025-10-12 07:00:00\"},\"c6ea490e-ad7d-401f-b119-1404e146ac0e\":{\"date\":\"2025-10-08 07:00:00\"},\"6cbe1a93-eb4b-48f0-b47c-fc314d657898\":false}', 1, '2025-08-11 11:04:01', '2025-08-11 11:04:01', '192eba49-693b-4bba-9a5a-66817e742c5d'),
