(1432, 1432, 1, NULL, '__temp_ywlgkxkukxuihgsqqikjcwvzhbseoihnjres', NULL, '{\"032378b9-225f-4ca4-b509-5bf5b952dde2\":\"Upcoming events / gatherings\",\"66af9589-1520-49a8-982e-6ddca319d308\":\"<h4>Resonant Touch Immersion&nbsp;- October 1012, Berlin</h4><p><strong>A three-day journey into the living field of Resonant Touch</strong></p><p>This immersion offers a relational and embodied space for therapists and practitioners to explore the essence of Resonant Touch. Its not a method to learn, but a shared inquirywhere body, presence, and awareness meet in the moment.</p><p>The work draws from two complementary sources:<br>B<strong>iodynamic&nbsp;Craniosacral&nbsp;Therapy</strong>, with its orientation to the subtle forces of life and healing, and the&nbsp;<strong>NARM approach</strong>&nbsp;to developmental trauma, which brings awareness to our patterns of self-relation and connection.</p><p>Together, we attune to the quiet intelligence at the heart of all healing. In this space, curiosity, connection, and spaciousness can naturally unfold.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p style=\\\"margin-left:0cm;\\\"><strong>What We Will Explore</strong></p><p>We begin by sensing the deeper intelligence of life forcea subtle, organizing movement within and around us. In the craniosacral tradition, this force supports coherence, wholeness, and healing.</p><p>As we meet it with presence and grounded awareness, we listen and respond rather than do or fix. The bodys own healing impulses can then emerge and be met.</p><p>Informed by NARM, we also explore how early adaptations shape our sense of selfand how these patterns live in our present-day therapeutic presence. We approach self-relation not as a concept, but as a lived experienceone that can shift when met with resonance, compassion, and inner safety.</p><p>Throughout the immersion theoratical input and perspectives are provided as orienting principles, and it largely experience-based.&nbsp;You are invited to trust your intuitive impulses and explore how they can be included with sensitivity and care.</p><p>An essential part of the work is about&nbsp;returning to your own sensing, being, and relating.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p style=\\\"margin-left:0cm;\\\"><strong>For Whom?</strong></p><p>This immersion is for:</p><ul><li>Therapists and healing practitioners (psychotherapists, bodyworkers, coaches)</li><li>Professionals working relationally with others</li><li>Anyone drawn to embodied, trauma-informed healing grounded in presence and subtle awareness</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Vec podatkov o seminarju je v flayerju (ki so ga organizatorke pripravile) ki ga bom poslal naknadno</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Resonant Touch Circle  November 8  9, Berlin</strong></p><p>Ongoing Relational Field of Practice</p><p>The Resonant Touch Circle is an ongoing small group of experienced practitioners engaged in long-term embodied exploration. Together, we meet regularly in a field of presence, resonance, and intuitive learning.</p><p>This group began in 2022 as a co-creative process without a formal structure, and over time, it became the ground from which the core principles of the Resonant Touch approach emerged. It remains a vital space of shared inquiry and mutual deepening.</p><p>This circle is not open to new members, but continues to evolve as a living, relational practice space.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Link: Read more about the circle and its members&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Individual supervisions</strong> support practitioners in their professional development from a relational perspective. NARM individual supervisions focus on the application of NARM principles in therapeutic work, exploring survival patterns, relational dynamics, emotional processing, and the therapists own embodied presence within the clinical setting. Resonant Touch individual supervisions are available for those who have trained in Resonant Touch with me, offering a space to deepen sensitivity to the life force, relational attunement, and awareness of how developmental and survival patterns are held within the body-mind.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Group supervisions</strong> are self-organized and provide a reflective space to explore therapeutic work in a supportive environment. We address the application of NARM principles in clinical practice, the navigation of countertransference dynamics, working through moments of stuckness, and developing comfort with the unknown. Participants bring case material, clinical questions, and personal reflections, fostering an environment for learning and mutual growth. Group supervisions can also be organized around specific themes related to NARM, offering more specific deep-dive explorations.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Active Coaching Groups</strong></p><p><i>For NARM Practitioners and Trainees</i></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>These guided, experiential groups are designed for NARM-trained practitioners and those currently in training who wish to deepen their embodied understanding of the model through presence, practice, and reflection.</p><p>Rather than focusing on technique, these sessions invite you into an environment of curiosity, safety, and authentic learning. Youre encouraged to explore your own therapeutic impulses and relational style in a way that feels natural and personally meaningful. We emphasize a non-judgmental, spacious atmosphere where insight can arise from within the relational field. The work unfolds organicallythrough shared presence, intuitive listening, and trust in what emerges.</p><p><strong>Practical Information</strong></p><p>These online Active Coaching sessions are designed for smaller groups (max. 8 participants) to allow for spaciousness, depth, and a supportive environment. Each session lasts approximately <strong>2.5 hours</strong> and includes time for <strong>two rounds of active coaching</strong>.</p><p>The <strong>fee is 60 EUR</strong>.</p><p>You are invited to bring your curiosity, openness, and willingness to explorethis is not about doing NARM right, but about discovering how it lives in you.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li><strong>NARM Online Active Coaching Group&nbsp;</strong></li></ul><p>October 8th at 17:30 CET, register</p><p>November 5th 17:30 CET, register</p><p>December 3ed at 17:30CET, register</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>NARM deepening days</strong></p><p><i>Exploring the Heart of NARM Through Immersive Practice</i></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>NARM Deepening Days are a dedicated space for those who wish to engage more fully with the principles of the NeuroAffective Relational Model (NARM). These days are designed for practitioners, students, and individuals already familiar with NARM who are looking to deepen their embodied understanding of this powerful model for healing developmental and relational trauma.</p><p>Each Deepening Day will focus on a specific theme central to the NARM approach.&nbsp;</p><p>These gatherings are <i>experiential and practice-oriented</i>, combining short teaching segments with reflective exercises, active coaching, and live demo sessions. The intention is to create a safe and focused environment for deepening insight, refining relational skills, and exploring how NARMs principles come alive in the moment-to-moment therapeutic process.</p><ul><li><strong>Life Force beyond Adaptations</strong> (online), to be announced</li><li><strong>Holding Without Fixing: The Role of Touch in a NARM-Oriented Process</strong> (at the venue), to be announced</li><li><strong>The Gift of Countertransference Dynamics</strong> (online), to be announced</li></ul>\",\"489bc2dc-2ddb-441d-8ddb-00351993c722\":true}', 1, '2025-08-11 11:19:08', '2025-08-11 11:19:08', '8630af64-b605-4aff-9660-cc537de19166'),
