atterns are held within the body-mind.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Group supervisions</strong> are self-organized and provide a reflective space to explore therapeutic work in a supportive environment. We address the application of NARM principles in clinical practice, the navigation of countertransference dynamics, working through moments of stuckness, and developing comfort with the unknown. Participants bring case material, clinical questions, and personal reflections, fostering an environment for learning and mutual growth. Group supervisions can also be organized around specific themes related to NARM, offering more specific deep-dive explorations.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Active Coaching Groups</strong></p><p><i>For NARM Practitioners and Trainees</i></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>These guided, experiential groups are designed for NARM-trained practitioners and those currently in training who wish to deepen their embodied understanding of the model through presence, practice, and reflection.</p><p>Rather than focusing on technique, these sessions invite you into an environment of curiosity, safety, and authentic learning. Youre encouraged to explore your own therapeutic impulses and relational style in a way that feels natural and personally meaningful. We emphasize a non-judgmental, spacious atmosphere where insight can arise from within the relational field. The work unfolds organicallythrough shared presence, intuitive listening, and trust in what emerges.</p><p><strong>Practical Information</strong></p><p>These online Active Coaching sessions are designed for smaller groups (max. 8 participants) to allow for spaciousness, depth, and a supportive environment. Each session lasts approximately <strong>2.5 hours</strong> and includes time for <strong>two rounds of active coaching</strong>.</p><p>The <strong>fee is 60 EUR</strong>.</p><p>You are invited to bring your curiosity, openness, and willingness to explorethis is not about doing NARM right, but about discovering how it lives in you.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li><strong>NARM Online Active Coaching Group&nbsp;</strong></li></ul><p>October 8th at 17:30 CET, register</p><p>November 5th 17:30 CET, register</p><p>December 3ed at 17:30CET, register</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>NARM deepening days</strong></p><p><i>Exploring the Heart of NARM Through Immersive Practice</i></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>NARM Deepening Days are a dedicated space for those who wish to engage more fully with the principles of the NeuroAffective Relational Model (NARM). These days are designed for practitioners, students, and individuals already familiar with NARM who are looking to deepen their embodied understanding of this powerful model for healing developmental and relational trauma.</p><p>Each Deepening Day will focus on a specific theme central to the NARM approach.&nbsp;</p><p>These gatherings are <i>experiential and practice-oriented</i>, combining short teaching segments with reflective exercises, active coaching, and live demo sessions. The intention is to create a safe and focused environment for deepening insight, refining relational skills, and exploring how NARMs principles come alive in the moment-to-moment therapeutic process.</p><ul><li><strong>Life Force beyond Adaptations</strong> (online), to be announced</li><li><strong>Holding Without Fixing: The Role of Touch in a NARM-Oriented Process</strong> (at the venue), to be announced</li><li><strong>The Gift of Countertransference Dynamics</strong> (online), to be announced</li></ul>\",\"489bc2dc-2ddb-441d-8ddb-00351993c722\":true}', 1, '2025-08-11 11:19:53', '2025-08-11 11:19:53', 'e7e483d3-369f-48bb-8748-d395aa60474d'),
